      "t": "p",
      "x": "POTENCY. Potency is the concentration (or dose) required to produce a given effect, indexed by EC50 — the concentration that produces 50% of the maximal response. A more potent drug needs less to do the job, so its curve sits further left. EFFICACY. Efficacy is the maximal effect the drug can achieve, indexed by Emax — how high the plateau goes, regardless of dose. The two are read off different axes (potency = x, efficacy = y) and are unrelated: a drug can be extremely potent yet have low efficacy, or need a big dose yet deliver a huge maximal effect."
