      "t": "p",
      "x": "THE RATIO. The therapeutic index is a measure of drug safety: TI = TD50 / ED50, the median toxic dose over the median effective dose. ED50 is the dose producing the therapeutic effect in 50% of the population; TD50 is the dose producing the toxic effect in 50%. A wider TI means a bigger gap between effective and toxic dosing — a safer drug. Parmar's intuition pump: over-the-counter products have high TI (you can buy them without a prescription precisely because accidental overdose is hard), while narrow-TI drugs demand careful dosing because a small step past the effective dose lands you in toxicity."
