      "t": "p",
      "x": "OVERVIEW. This LO is about reading what a drug does to a receptor and recognizing the fingerprint each behavior leaves on the dose-response curve. The vocabulary splits cleanly: agonists activate (full, partial, or inverse), and antagonists block (competitive or non-competitive). Two ideas do the heavy lifting — intrinsic activity (how much response a bound drug produces) and what happens to potency versus Emax when you add a blocker."
