      "t": "p",
      "x": "THE MAOI INTERACTION — the headline. MAO inhibitors block catecholamine breakdown, so synaptic and stored NE is already high. Add an indirect releaser — ephedrine, amphetamine, or dietary tyramine — and you dump more NE onto an unbuffered system → hypertensive crisis. That is why ephedrine is contraindicated during or within 14 days of an MAOI, and why the tyramine ‘cheese reaction’ happens. This single principle covers most of the LO."
