      "x": "OVERVIEW. This is the largest drug roster in the composite, and Parmar’s strategy is explicit: lean on the suffix and the mnemonics. The suffix is “-olol” = β-blocker, with exactly two exceptions — labetalol and carvedilol, the mixed α/β agents. Then three groups, each with its own mnemonic."
