      "x": "OVERVIEW. The polymyxins are the odd ones out: they don’t touch the cell wall at all — they disrupt the cell membrane like a detergent. Two are used, polymyxin B and polymyxin E (colistin), and they are active only against gram-negative rods, including Pseudomonas. Mostly topical, but colistin has been revived as an IV last resort for multidrug-resistant gram-negatives."
