      "x": "OVERVIEW. Trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole (Bactrim, Septra; abbreviated TMP-SMX) is the clinical embodiment of sequential folate blockade — a folate-reduction inhibitor and a folate-synthesis inhibitor in one tablet, synergistic because they hit two steps of the same pathway. The fixed combination is typically 160 mg trimethoprim / 800 mg sulfamethoxazole. This is the highest-yield drug in the lecture, so anchor on its first-line uses."
